President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on Law Day, which is celebrated on May 1st. The proclamation highlights the importance of the rule of law in the United States and celebrates the country's heritage of liberty, justice, and equality under the law. It emphasizes the significance of the Constitution and its establishment of a unique structure of government with separate branches to prevent the concentration of power. The proclamation also mentions the 150th anniversary of the ratification of the Fourteenth Amendment, which guarantees equal protection and due process of law. It calls for a rededication to the rule of law and encourages Americans to reflect upon its importance. The proclamation urges government officials, the legal profession, the press, and media industries to support and participate in the observance of Law Day.